A lawyer for Gerard Depardieu today claimed that his prosecution for drink driving was illegal – because the actor was ‘not completely sober’ when he was told about it.

During bizarre proceedings in a Paris criminal court, defence barrister Eric de Caumont admitted the Hollywood actor had been drinking champagne before he fell off his moped in the city last November.

But by the time he was questioned by detectives and then charged he was still too drunk to understand what was going on.

Mr De Caumont’s claims were denied by Paris police who said in a statement that Depardieu was ‘conscious, lucid and able to respond’ when he was charged.

